      "content": "It makes sense to feel this way when the connection to who you used to be feels completely severed, leaving you to wonder if you've been living the wrong life all along. While the pain of feeling like a mistake is overwhelming, trying to force a spark back into a void that feels dead often leads to more frustration than healing. You are still here, enduring the weight of an empty vessel, and that persistence, even when it feels pointless, is what proves that only a tiny part of you remains.",
